## Handling Transition from Framework to CSOC

### Week 1-2: Run Framework Only
```
- Deploy Framework 7 analytics
- Use Framework 10 use cases
- Use Framework 8 automation rules
- Basic JIRA fields only
- Team gets comfortable with core workflow
```

**Success metrics:**
- âœ“ Alerts firing consistently
- âœ“ JIRA tickets auto-creating
- âœ“ Analysts following playbooks
- âœ“ Team confident with process

### Week 3: Add CSOC Fields (Transition Week)
```
- Monday: Add all CSOC custom fields to JIRA
- Tuesday: Configure new fields in automation rules
- Wednesday: Test with sample data
- Thursday: Update automation rules with new field logic
- Friday: Train team on new fields
```

**Minimal disruption:**
- Existing alerts keep working
- New alerts auto-populate more fields
- Team gradually learns new field purposes

### Weeks 4-8: Build Out CSOC Use Cases
```
- Continue deploying Framework analytics
- Start building 100+ use cases in Confluence
- Update automation rules with new logic
- Build SOC Asset Intelligence as discoveries happen
- Team becomes more effective with comprehensive knowledge
```

