## CSOC-Specific Enhancements to Framework

### 1. Policy Violation Handling
Framework provides incident response. CSOC adds:
```
New workflow: Policy Violation (not security incident)
â”œâ”€ No Change Ticket
â”œâ”€ Change Outside Window  
â”œâ”€ Expired Change Ticket
â””â”€ Policy Bypass

Separate from malicious incidents â†’ Different escalation
```

### 2. Asset Documentation
Framework assumes documented assets. CSOC adds:
```
New custom field: Asset Documentation Status
â”œâ”€ Documented (expected)
â”œâ”€ Undocumented (discovered through investigation)
â””â”€ Legacy (known older systems)

Generates Asset Investigation Requests for undocumented systems
```

### 3. Shift Awareness
Framework mentions 12-hour shifts. CSOC adds:
```
New custom field: Shift
â”œâ”€ Day (06:00-18:00)
â”œâ”€ Night (18:00-06:00)
â””â”€ Rotating

Auto-assignment based on current shift
Handoff procedure between shifts
```

### 4. Shadow IT Discovery
Framework provides detection. CSOC adds:
```
Confluence: SOC Asset Intelligence
â”œâ”€ Servers (discovered during investigations)
â”œâ”€ Applications (unknown apps found)
â””â”€ Network Segments (undocumented)

Built collaboratively over time
Reduces undocumented systems over time
```

