## Key Differences & How to Handle Them

### Framework Simplicity vs. CSOC Comprehensiveness

| Aspect | Framework | CSOC | Resolution |
|--------|-----------|------|-----------|
| **Use Cases** | 10 core cases | 100+ comprehensive cases | Start with 10, expand weekly |
| **Custom Fields** | 7-8 essential | 28+ comprehensive | Add Week 3 |
| **Workflows** | Single alert flow | 3 specialized workflows | Update Week 3 |
| **Documentation** | Core concepts | Deep technical details | Reference as needed |
| **Asset Intelligence** | Not included | Central Confluence | Build as you go |
| **Policy Violations** | Security incidents only | Separate workflow | Implement Week 3 |

### Transition Approach
```
PHASE 1 (Weeks 1-2): Framework Only
â”œâ”€ Deploy, train, stabilize
â”œâ”€ Prove value quickly
â””â”€ Build analyst confidence

TRANSITION (Week 3): Add CSOC
â”œâ”€ Add fields all at once
â”œâ”€ Migrate to detailed workflows
â”œâ”€ Enable more automation
â””â”€ Team adapts gradually

PHASE 2 (Weeks 4-8): CSOC Full
â”œâ”€ Build 100+ use cases
â”œâ”€ Leverage all fields
â”œâ”€ Advanced automation
â””â”€ Comprehensive coverage
```

---

## Questions This Integration Answers

**Q: How do I deploy both?**
A: Framework first (2 weeks), then CSOC expansion (6 weeks). No conflict.

**Q: Do I need all 28 custom fields?**
A: No. Framework requires 7-8. Add CSOC fields in Week 3 when you're ready.

**Q: Can I use just the Framework?**
A: Yes. It's production-ready as-is. CSOC guide adds depth and coverage.

**Q: Should I deploy all 100+ use cases?**
A: No. Start with Framework 10, add CSOC use cases as analytics mature.

**Q: How do I handle the different workflows?**
A: Framework provides single flow. Implement CSOC 3-flow system in Week 3.

**Q: What about Confluence?**
A: Framework docs can go in Confluence directly. Use CSOC structure for organization.

---

